   Aug 28 2016

LoRaWAN Node Shields

   My new LoRaWAN node also comes with additional shields to realize the
   most crazy projects. They are available for order with the any version
   of the node.

   All shields are the same size as the node and are connected with two
   regular 14 pin headers.
   At the moment I developed 3 shields:
     * Proto shield
          + Proto area
          + Load switching mosfet circuit controlled by digital pin to
            power on/off external electronics. With power-on LED.

   TvB LoRaWAN Proto Shield Rev.2 - Preview
     * RTC shield
          + DS3231 with 3V backup battery.
            The DS3231 also has a programmable interrupt output to wake up
            the LoRaWAN node every X seconds, minutes, hours, …
          + Small proto area
          + Load switching mosfet circuit controlled by digital pin to
            power on/off external electronics. With power-on LED.

   TvB LoRaWAN Node RTC Shield Rev.1 - Preview
     * RTC & GPS shield
          + DS3231 with battery backup
          + Ultra small GPS module (OriginGPS Nano/Micro Hornet) with
            onboard, buildin GPS/GLONASS antenna
          + Small proto area
          + Load switching mosfet circuit controlled by digital pin to
            power on/off external electronics

   TvB LoRaWAN Node RTC + GPS Shield Rev.1 - Preview

   The RTC/GPS node is only available without GPS module

